We love good Soup with Rocket and Pesto and this deliciously simple, chef-curated
recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} on a lined
#baking tray{} and drizzle on a splash of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and charred at the
edges, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).
Halve the @yellow pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small
pieces. Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways), then quarter
lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate
the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and
rinse the @cannellini beans{1}.

Heat a splash of oil in large, deep #saucepan{} on medium heat. When hot, add
the onion, carrot and pepper. Cook until beginning to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}
then add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @ground coriander{1/2%tsp} and
@dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding the
@water{500%ml} and the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to a boil, then reduce
the heat to low and simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @basil{} stalks and all and half the @wild rocket{20%g}. Pop the
basil, chopped rocket and @walnuts{20}(roughly chopped) in a #small bowl{} and
use the end of a #rolling pin{} to roughly mash them together.

> TIP: Use a #pestle and mortar{} if you have one!

Stir in the @olive oil{1%tbsp}, you should have a rough, thick paste. Season to
taste with a little salt and pepper. Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into
small pieces) into small pieces.

Add the cannellini beans and @chopped cavolo nero{100%g} to the soup and simmer
until the cavolo nero has softened, ~{5%minutes}. Season the soup to taste with
salt and pepper and just before serving, stir in the chopped vine tomato.

Ladle the soup into deep #bowls{} and spoon small amounts of the pesto on top for
stirring in. Top with the cauliflower florets. Finish with the remaining
rocket. Buono apettito!